# Claude Command Centre — Cursor Rules

## Repo Overview

This is a Claude Code plugin repo using spec-driven development. All plugin content definitions (skills/agents/commands) are written in YAML/Markdown — no TypeScript or compiled code.

## Structure

- `agents/` — Agent definitions (9 agents)
- `commands/` — Slash commands (19 commands)
- `skills/` — Skill definitions (39 skills)
- `hooks/` — Session and tool hooks
- `styles/` — Output style definitions
- `templates/` — Linear issue/document templates (JSON)
- `.claude-plugin/` — Plugin manifest (plugin.json, marketplace.json)

## File Conventions

- Skills: `skills/<name>/SKILL.md` with YAML frontmatter (`name`, `description` required)
- Agents: `agents/<name>.md` with YAML frontmatter (`name`, `description`, `allowedTools`)
- Commands: `commands/<name>.md` with YAML frontmatter (`description` required)
- Templates: `templates/<name>.json` conforming to `templates/schema.json`
- Minimum skill depth: 8192 characters

## Forbidden

- No API keys, tokens, or secrets in any file
- No TypeScript or compiled code
- No duplicate skills — check `marketplace.json` first
- No direct push to `main` — PR + squash merge only
- No bundling multiple Linear issues into one PR
- Do not modify `plugin.json` version without explicit instruction

## Testing

Run before submitting: `bash tests/test-static-quality.sh`

## Git

- Branch naming: `{agent}/{issue-id}-{slug}`
- One PR per Linear issue (CIA-XXX)
- Include `Closes CIA-XXX` in PR body
